    <bibl><title>Die Abendpost</title>,
<date when="1890-10-15">October 15, 1890</date>.
<title level="a">THE GERMAN LANGUAGE IN THE SCHOOLS</title></bibl>
   </div>
  </front>
  <body>
   <p>Out of 40,796 pupils in schools where German is taught, 26,801 pupils took up the study of German during the month of September.</p>
   <p>Of these 26,801 pupils: 12,268 are of German parentage: 7,773 of Angelo-American and 6,760 of Irish, Scandinavian, Bohemian, etc.</p>
   <p>The German instruction is given by 191 teachers.</p>
